legacy.full_text: From January to September, 2023, China’s outbound direct investment (ODI) kept growing, with non-financial ODI reaching USD96.0 billion, up 11.8% y-o-y. Specifically, Chinese companies’ non-financial ODI in Belt and Road countries amounted to USD23.5 billion, up 20.3% y-o-y. https://t.co/vG6JuMOf3T

legacy.full_text: The sixth China International Import Expo will be held in Shanghai from November 5 to 10. This year, the CIIE is expected to gather participants from 154 countries, regions and international organizations. 3,486 exhibitors and 408,000 buyers have signed up for the Expo. https://t.co/gsag4mn6rH

legacy.full_text: The scale of the 134th Canton Fair (Phase Ⅲ) has hit a record high. Covering a total area of 515,000 square meters with more than 24,000 booths, the fair has attracted over 11,000 exhibitors and presented around 990,000 exhibits online. https://t.co/yfDUJzL4ip

In recent years, China-ASEAN trade and economic cooperation has been taken to a higher level with fruitful outcomes.
Thanks to the dividends released by RCEP, steady progress has been made in the building of China-ASEAN Free Trade Area. https://t.co/nJXoECXSR5

legacy.description: Welcome to the official account of the Ministry of Commerce of the People's Republic of China.

legacy.full_text: As the largest trading partners of each other, China and ASEAN have consolidated their trade ties, with bilateral trade growing 11.2% y-o-y to USD975.3 billion in 2022, a 1.2-fold increase from USD443.6 billion in 2013.

legacy.description: Welcome to the official account of the Ministry of Commerce of the People's Republic of China.
legacy.name: 中华人民共和国商务部MOFCOM

legacy.full_text: China and ASEAN are major sources and destinations of investment for each other. As of July 2023, two-way investment between the two sides exceeded USD380 billion, and over 6,500 companies with direct Chinese investment were set up in ASEAN.

legacy.full_text: The 20th China-ASEAN Expo (CAEXPO) will be held in Nanning, Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region from September 16 to 19, under the theme of “Work together for a harmonious home and a shared future: promoting high quality development of the BRI and nurturing new epicenter of growth”.

legacy.description: Welcome to the official account of the Ministry of Commerce of the People's Republic of China.
legacy.name: 中华人民共和国商务部MOFCOM

legacy.full_text: This year’s Expo will gather more than 40 countries and nearly 1,700 companies, with the exhibition area of foreign participants accounting for over 30% of the total. Various trade and economic events will also be held during the Expo. @CaexpoOnline

legacy.description: Welcome to the official account of the Ministry of Commerce of the People's Republic of China.

legacy.full_text: @CaexpoOnline We sincerely welcome friends from all sectors, both at home and abroad, to join the CAEXPO to forge greater synergy in the spirit of innovation and pursue common development.

legacy.full_text: Brazil, Serbia and Qatar will be the three countries of honor of the 2023 CIFIT. So far, nearly 40 foreign government officials at or above the vice-ministerial level have confirmed their participation.

legacy.full_text: Around 1,000 business groups and 80,000 business visitors from nearly 100 countries and regions are expected to attend the fair.
